# Backend API (Django)
# Local development API. For production builds this must be a publicly
# reachable API origin, not localhost.
VITE_API_URL=http://localhost:8000

# Public API origin. Used only when this same bundle is served from a public
# host (e.g. the Cloudflare tunnel at www.zeldathon.co.uk) while VITE_API_URL
# above is still the loopback dev address — resolveApiUrl() (src/lib/env.ts)
# switches to this so the public site reaches the right backend. Leave unset
# for a pure local checkout.
VITE_PUBLIC_API_URL=https://api.zeldathon.co.uk

# Clerk publishable keys. Because one dev server serves both localhost and the
# public tunnel domain, resolveClerkKey() (src/lib/env.ts) picks by page host:
#  - VITE_CLERK_PUBLISHABLE_KEY: the DEV Clerk instance (pk_test_…), used on
#    localhost. A prod (pk_live_…) key can't sign in on localhost.
#  - VITE_PUBLIC_CLERK_PUBLISHABLE_KEY: the PROD Clerk instance (pk_live_…), used
#    when served from the public domain (www.zeldathon.co.uk).
# Set both for full dev+prod auth; leaving both blank disables auth (control
# panel unreachable, public site/overlays still work).
VITE_CLERK_PUBLISHABLE_KEY=
VITE_PUBLIC_CLERK_PUBLISHABLE_KEY=
